I guess I wasn't clear.  What you say is true, but my point is that we must use our power to change the government and in Viet Nam we didn't do that.<br>
  We ignored the corruption and did not FORCE the government to change and we could have used our power to do that.<br>
   The same with China.  They want &quot;most favored nation&quot; status then link it to social change.  They don't then we don't recognize them as such.  Would cost us--but it will work.  Not everyone understands compassion--everyone understands power, but only if it's used.<br><br>
